Intro

Counting the number of objects that satisfy certain criteria.

Problem: link

The Rule of Product

Tutorial: link

  • If we have three nodes — a,ba, ba,b and ccc — and there are 444 roads from aaa to bbb and 555 roads from bbb to ccc, then we can get from aaa to ccc through bbb in r∗5=20r*5=20r∗5=20 different ways.
  • How many subsets are there in an array of nnn integers?
  • How many non-empty subsets are there in an array of nnn integers?
  • How many positive divisors does 2000=24⋅532000 = 2^4 \cdot 5^32000=24⋅53 have?
  • Given an array of nnn integers. Find the number of subsequences where each element is distinct. Problem: link

The Rule of Sum

If there are mmm ways to arrange something, and there are nnn ways to arrange something else, and these arrangements cannot both happen, then the number of ways to arrange either of those things is m+nm + nm+n.

  • Find the number of different binary sequences of length nnn such that no two 0’s are adjacent.

Double Counting

Double counting is an error in which the same object or arrangement is counted more than once.

  • How many integers between 111 and 10910^9109 are divisible by 333 or 555?
  • How many integers between 111 and 10910^9109 are divisible by 666 or 888?

Permutations

A permutation is an arrangement of objects with regard to order.

  • How many permutations are there? Why?
  • Find the number of possible choices of kkk objects from a set of nnn objects when order is important and one object can be chosen more than once.
  • Permutations of choosing rrr distinct objects out of a collection of nnn objects: P(n,r)=?P(n, r) = ?P(n,r)=?. Note that permutation means order matters. That is (1,2,3)(1, 2, 3)(1,2,3) and (1,3,2)(1, 3, 2)(1,3,2) are different.
  • Permutations with Repetitions: Find the number of different permutations of nnn objects, where there are n1n_1n1​ indistinguishable objects of type 111, n2n_2n2​ indistinguishable objects of type 222,…, and nkn_knk​ indistinguishable objects of type k(n1+n2+…+nk=n)k (n_1+n_2+ \ldots +n_k=n)k(n1​+n2​+…+nk​=n). Tutorial: link.
  • Find the number of different permutations of an array of n≤105n \le 10^5n≤105 integers.
  • Find the number of anagrams of a string.
  • Restrictions on Adjacent Objects: Find the number of different permutations of nnn objects, where there are n1n_1n1​ indistinguishable objects of type 111, n2n_2n2​ indistinguishable objects of type 222,…, and nkn_knk​ indistinguishable objects of type k(n1+n2+…+nk=n)k (n_1+n_2+ \ldots +n_k=n)k(n1​+n2​+…+nk​=n) but there is one restriction: all elements of same type have to be adjacent to each other.

Next Permutation

Tutorial - link, Problem - link.

You can generate all permutations of nnn elements by repeatedly using next_permutation.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n = 5;
  vector<int> p;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    p.push_back(i);
  }
  do {
    // do something on p
    for (auto x: p) cout << x << ' '; cout << '\n';
  } while (next_permutation(p.begin(), p.end()));
  return 0;
}

Combinations

A combination is an arrangement of objects without regard to order. In combinations, we choose a set of elements (rather than an arrangement, as in permutations) so the order doesn’t matter.

  • Given a set of nnn distinct objects, Find the number of combinations of kkk of those objects where each element can be selected exactly once. C(n,k)=?C(n, k) = ?C(n,k)=?.
  • C(n,k)=C(n,n−k)C(n, k) = C(n, n - k)C(n,k)=C(n,n−k).
  • What is the maximum value of C(n,i)C(n, i)C(n,i) over all 0≤i≤n0 \le i \le n0≤i≤n.
  • C(n,k)=C(n−1,k−1)+C(n−1,k)C(n, k) = C(n - 1, k - 1) + C(n - 1, k)C(n,k)=C(n−1,k−1)+C(n−1,k). What is the intuitive proof of this?
  • C(n,k)C(n, k)C(n,k) is also called the binomial coefficient.
  • Find the number of binary integers of length nnn and with kkk 1's.
  • Find the number of ordered pairs (a,b)(a, b)(a,b) of binary sequences of length nnn, such that the distance between them is kkk. The distance is the number of positions such that aaa and bbb have different bits at that position.
  • You can generate all combinations of rrr elements of an array of length nnn using backtracking or bitmasks.

Stars and Bars

Tutorial: link

  • Find the number of kkk-tuples of non-negative integers whose sum is nnn. That is - find the number solutions to the equation a1+a2+…+ak=na_1 + a_2 + \ldots + a_k = na1​+a2​+…+ak​=n such that all ai≥0a_i \ge 0ai​≥0.
  • Find the number of kkk-tuples of positive integers whose sum is nnn. That is - find the number solutions to the equation a1+a2+…+ak=na_1 + a_2 + \ldots + a_k = na1​+a2​+…+ak​=n such that all ai≥1a_i \ge 1ai​≥1.
  • Find the number solutions to the equation a1+a2+…+ak=na_1 + a_2 + \ldots + a_k = na1​+a2​+…+ak​=n such that a1≥l1,a2≥l2,…,ak≥lka_1 \ge l_1, a_2 \ge l_2, \ldots , a_k \ge l_ka1​≥l1​,a2​≥l2​,…,ak​≥lk​.

Garbage Partition

Find the number solutions to the equation a1+a2+…+ak≤na_1 + a_2 + \ldots + a_k \le na1​+a2​+…+ak​≤n where all ai≥0a_i \ge 0ai​≥0.

Coding Time

Given qqq queries of type (n,k)(n, k)(n,k), find P(n,k)P(n, k)P(n,k) and C(n,k)C(n, k)C(n,k) modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7. Constraints: 1≤q,n,k≤1061 \le q, n, k \le 10^61≤q,n,k≤106.

Problem: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e6, mod = 1e9 + 7;

int power(long long n, long long k) {
  int ans = 1 % mod; n %= mod; if (n < 0) n += mod;
  while (k) {
    if (k & 1) ans = (long long) ans * n % mod;
    n = (long long) n * n % mod;
    k >>= 1;
  }
  return ans;
}
int f[N], invf[N];
int nCr(int n, int r) {
  if (n < r or n < 0) return 0;
  return 1LL * f[n] * invf[r] % mod * invf[n - r] % mod;
}
int nPr(int n, int r) {
  if (n < r or n < 0) return 0;
  return 1LL * f[n] * invf[n - r] % mod;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  f[0] = 1;
  for (int i = 1; i < N; i++) {
    f[i] = 1LL * i * f[i - 1] % mod;
  }
  invf[N - 1] = power(f[N - 1], mod - 2);
  for (int i = N - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
    invf[i] = 1LL * invf[i + 1] * (i + 1) % mod;
  }
  cout << nCr(6, 2) << '\n';
  cout << nPr(6, 2) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Pascal's Triangle

Tutorial: link, link2

Properties:

  • This is same is Binomial Coefficients. Why?
  • ∑i=0nC(n,i)=2n\sum_{i = 0}^{n}{C(n, i)} = 2^n∑i=0n​C(n,i)=2n
  • ∑i≥0C(n,2i)=2n−1\sum_{i \ge 0}{C(n, 2i)} = 2^{n - 1}∑i≥0​C(n,2i)=2n−1
  • ∑i≥0C(n,2i+1)=2n−1\sum_{i \ge 0}{C(n, 2i + 1)} = 2^{n - 1}∑i≥0​C(n,2i+1)=2n−1

There are lots of other properties of this triangle, we will learn more about them later.

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1010, mod = 1e9 + 7;
int C[N][N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  C[0][0] = 1;
  for (int n = 1; n < N; n++) {
    C[n][0] = 1;
    for (int k = 1; k <= n; k++) {
      C[n][k] = (C[n - 1][k - 1] + C[n - 1][k]) % mod;
    }
  }
  cout << C[6][2] << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Binomial Theorem

What is the intuitive proof of the formula?

Hint: Think about nnn boxes where each box contains two elements named aaa and bbb.

Relation to Pascals Triangle:

  • ∑i=0nki⋅C(n,i)=(k+1)n\sum_{i = 0}^{n}{k^i \cdot C(n, i)} = (k + 1)^n∑i=0n​ki⋅C(n,i)=(k+1)n. Why?

1. Problem A

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;

void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	int ara[n + 1];
	map<int, int> mp;
	for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
		cin >> ara[i];
		mp[ara[i]]++;
	}
	ll ans = 1;
	for (auto i : mp) {
		ans = ((ans % mod) * ((i.second + 1) % mod)) % mod;
	}
	cout << ans - 1 << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

2. Problem B

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include "H:\code\codeforces\debug.h"
#else
#define debug(...)
#define sdebug(...)
#endif

const int N = (int)2e5 + 5;
const ll mod = 998244353;

ll mul(ll a, ll b) {
	return ((a % mod) * (b % mod)) % mod;
}

vector<ll> fact;

void precalcfact(ll x) {
  fact.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
}

int n;
vector<int> adj[N];
ll ans = 1;
int children[N];

void dfs(int node, int par) {
	for (int u : adj[node]) {
		if (u != par) {children[node]++; dfs(u, node);}
	}
}

void solve() {
	cin >> n;
	for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
		int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
		adj[u].push_back(v);
		adj[v].push_back(u);
	}
	dfs(1, -1);
//	sdebug(children, n);
	ans = mul(ans, fact[children[1]]);
	for (int i = 2; i <= n; ++i) {
		ans = mul(ans, fact[children[i] + 1]);
	}
	ans = mul(ans, n);
	cout << ans << "\n";
}

int main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
    cin.tie(0);
    precalcfact(N);
    int t = 1; 
//    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

int nC2(int n) {
	return n * (n - 1) / 2;
}

void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	char grid[n + 1][n + 1];
	for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
		for (int j = 1; j <= n; ++j) cin >> grid[i][j];
	}
	int ans = 0;
	for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
		int cnt = 0;
		for (int j = 1; j <= n; ++j) {
			if (grid[i][j] == 'C') cnt++;
		}
		ans += nC2(cnt);
	}
	for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
		int cnt = 0;
		for (int j = 1; j <= n; ++j) {
			if (grid[j][i] == 'C') cnt++;
		}
		ans += nC2(cnt);
	}
	cout << ans << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
//    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

8. Problem H

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif


void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	vector<ll> ans;
	for (int k = 1; k <= 10; ++k) {
		for (int mask = 0; mask < (1 << k); ++mask) {
			ll prev = 0;
			for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
				if (mask & (1 << i)) {
					prev *= 10;
					prev += 7;
				} else {
					prev *= 10;
					prev += 4;
				}
			}
			ans.push_back(prev);
		}	
	}
	sort(ans.begin(), ans.end());
	cout << lower_bound(ans.begin(), ans.end(), n) - ans.begin() + 1 << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
  //  cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

9. Problem I

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;

ll bigmod(ll a, ll b) {
  ll result = 1;
  while (b) {
    if (b & 1)
      result = ((result % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    a = ((a % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    b >>= 1;
  }
  return result;
}

void solve() {
	ll n, k; cin >> n >> k;
	cout << bigmod(n, k) << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

12. Problem L

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

const int N = 2005;
const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;

int n, k;
ll dp[N][N];

ll func(int indx, int len) {
	if (len == k) return 1;
	if (indx > n) return len == k;
	if (dp[indx][len] != -1) return dp[indx][len];
	ll ans = 0;
	for (int j = 1; j * indx <= n; ++j) {
		ans = ((ans % mod) + (func(indx * j, len + 1) % mod)) % mod;
	}
//	ans = ((ans % mod) + (func(indx + 1, len) % mod)) % mod;
	return dp[indx][len] = ans;
}
void solve() {
	cin >> n >> k;
	memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
	cout << func(1, 0) % mod << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
//   cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

13. Problem M

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include "H:\code\codeforces\debug.h"
#else
#define debug(...)
#define sdebug(...)
#endif


void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	int pre[n + 1];
	pre[0] = 1;
	for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
		int x; cin >> x;
		if (x < 0) pre[i] = -1;
		else pre[i] = 1;
		pre[i] *= pre[i - 1];
	}
	ll neg = 0, curNeg = 0, curPos = 1;
	for (int i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
		if (pre[i] < 0) {
			neg += curPos;
			curNeg++;
		} else {
			neg += curNeg;
			curPos++;
		}
	}
	ll pos = (1LL * n * (n + 1)) / 2 - neg;
	cout << neg << " " << pos << "\n";
}

int main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
    cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
  //  cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

14. Problem N

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

int modOne(int x) {
    return x / 3 + (x % 3 == 1) + (((x - 1) % 3) == 1);
}

int modTwo(int x) {
     return x / 3 + (x % 3 == 2);
}

int modZero(int x) {
    return (x - 1) / 3 + (x % 3 == 0 && x != 0);
}

const int N = (int)2e5 + 5;

ll n, l, r, zero, one, two;
ll dp[N][4];

const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;

ll func(int indx, int sum) {
	if (indx == n + 1) return sum == 0;
	if (dp[indx][sum] != -1) return dp[indx][sum];
	ll way = 0;
	way = ((one % mod) * (func(indx + 1, (sum + 1) % 3)) % mod) % mod;
	way = ((way % mod) + (((two % mod) * (func(indx + 1, (sum + 2) % 3)) % mod) % mod)) % mod;
	way = ((way % mod) + (((zero % mod) * (func(indx + 1, (sum + 0) % 3)) % mod) % mod)) % mod;
	return dp[indx][sum] = way;
}
void solve() {
	cin >> n >> l >> r;
	memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
	zero = modZero(r) - modZero(l - 1), one = modOne(r) - modOne(l - 1), two = modTwo(r) - modTwo(l - 1);
//	debug(zero, one, two);
	cout << func(1, 0) % mod << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
//    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

15. Problem O

void solve() {
	string x, y; cin >> x >> y;
	int nx = (int)x.size(), ny = (int)y.size();
	vector<pair<int, int > > pre;
	int cnt0 = 0, cnt1 = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < ny; ++i) {
		if (y[i] == '0') cnt0++;
		else cnt1++;
		pre.push_back({cnt0, cnt1});
	}
	ll ans = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < nx; ++i) {
		int hiIndx = ny - nx + i;
		if (x[i] == '0') {
			if(i - 1 >= 0) ans += pre[hiIndx].second - pre[i - 1].second;
			else ans += pre[hiIndx].second;
		} else {
			if (i - 1 >= 0) ans += pre[hiIndx].first - pre[i - 1].first;
			else ans += pre[hiIndx].first;
		}
	}
	cout << ans << "\n";
}

	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1;

17. Problem Q

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;
const ll N = (ll)1e5;

vector<ll> fact, invmod;

ll bigmod(ll a, ll b) {
  ll result = 1;
  while (b) {
    if (b & 1)
      result = ((result % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    a = ((a % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    b >>= 1;
  }
  return result;
}

void precalcfact(ll x) {
  fact.assign(x, 0);
  invmod.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  invmod[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
  invmod[x-1] = bigmod(fact[x-1], mod-2);
  for(ll i = x-2; i >= 1; --i) invmod[i] = ((invmod[i+1]%mod)*((i+1)%mod))%mod;
}
 
ll now(ll n, ll i) {
	return (((fact[n] % mod) * (invmod[n - i] % mod) % mod) * (invmod[i] % mod)) % mod;
}

void solve() {
	ll n; cin >> n;
	precalcfact(N + 2);
	ll ans = 0;
	for (ll i = 0; i <= n; ++i) {
		ll cur = 0;
		if (i == 0 || i == n) {
			cur = bigmod(6, n - i) % mod;
		} else {
			cur = ((bigmod(6, n - i) % mod) * (now(n, i) % mod)) % mod;
			//debug(cur);
		}
		ans  = ((ans % mod) + (cur % mod)) % mod;
	}
	//debug(bigmod(3, 3 * n), ans);
	cout << ((bigmod(3, 3 * n) % mod) - (ans % mod) + mod) % mod << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
 //   cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

18. Problem R

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
//Credit : https://codeforces.com/contest/1420/submission/93708229
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;

const ll mod=998244353;
const ll MX=3e5+5;
vector< ll > start, finish;

ll big_mod(ll n_, ll p_, ll mod_){
     if(p_==0) return 1LL;
     if(p_&1LL) return (n_*big_mod(n_, p_-1LL, mod_))%mod_;
     ll tmp_=big_mod(n_, p_>>1LL, mod_);
     return (tmp_*tmp_)%mod;
}

ll inverse_mod(ll n_, ll mod_){ return big_mod(n_, mod_-2, mod_); }

///Calculates nCr%mod
///pre_calc_fact() function must be called

ll fact[MX];

void pre_calc_fact(ll n_, ll mod_){
     fact[0]=1;
     for(ll i=1; i<=n_; ++i) fact[i]=(fact[i-1]*i)%mod_;
}

ll nCr(ll n_, ll r_, ll mod_){
     if(r_>n_) return 0;
     assert(fact[0]);
     return (fact[n_]*inverse_mod((fact[r_]*fact[n_-r_])%mod_, mod_))%mod_;
}

int main(){
     ll i, j, k;
     ll n;
     scanf("%lld %lld", &n, &k);
     for(i=0; i<n; ++i){
          ll l, r;
          scanf("%lld %lld", &l, &r);
          start.push_back(l);
          finish.push_back(r);
     }
     pre_calc_fact(n, mod);
     sort(start.begin(), start.end());
     sort(finish.begin(), finish.end());
     ll ans=0, prev_cnt=0, prev_val=-1;
     for(auto x:finish){
          if(x==prev_val) prev_cnt++;
          else prev_cnt=0;
          ll rem=upper_bound(start.begin(), start.end(), x)-start.begin();
          rem-=lower_bound(finish.begin(), finish.end(), x)-finish.begin();
          rem-=prev_cnt;
          ans=(ans+nCr(rem-1, k-1, mod))%mod;
          prev_val=x;
     }
     printf("%lld\n", ans);
}

19. Problem S

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

struct point {
	int x, y;
	bool operator <(const point &L) {
		if (x == L.x) return y < L.y;
		return x < L.x;
	}
};

double fun(int x1, int x2, int y1, int y2) {
	double cur = (x2 - x1) * (x2 - x1) + (y2 - y1) * (y2 - y1);
	return sqrt(cur);
}

void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	vector<point> vec(n);
	for (auto &i : vec) cin >> i.x >> i.y;
	sort(vec.begin(), vec.end());
   // for (auto i : vec) cerr << i.x << " " << i.y << "\n";
	double tot = 0;
	int fac = 0;
	do {
		double cur = 0;
		for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; ++i) {
			double calc = fun(vec[i].x, vec[i + 1].x, vec[i].y, vec[i + 1].y);
			cur += calc;
		}
		tot += cur;
		fac++;
	} while(next_permutation(vec.begin(), vec.end()));
//	debug(fac);
	cout << fixed << setprecision(10);
	cout << tot / (fac * 1.00) << "\n";

}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
   // cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

ll func(int r, int c, int rooks) {
	if (rooks > r || rooks > c) return 0;
	if (rooks == 0) return 1;
	if (r == 0) return c;
	if (c == 0) return r;
	if (dp[r][c][rooks] != -1) return dp[r][c][rooks];
	ll ans = r * func(r - 1, c - 1, rooks - 1);

}

		}
	}
	print_case;
	cout << func(n, n, k) << "\n";
}

23. Problem W

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include "H:\code\codeforces\debug.h"
#else
#define debug(...)
#define sdebug(...)
#endif

const int N = (int)1e6 + 1;
const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;

int T = 1;

vector<ll> fact, invmod;

ll bigmod(ll a, ll b) {
  ll result = 1;
  while (b) {
    if (b & 1)
      result = ((result % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    a = ((a % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    b >>= 1;
  }
  return result;
}

void precalcfact(ll x) {
  fact.assign(x, 0);
  invmod.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  invmod[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
  invmod[x - 1] = bigmod(fact[x - 1], mod - 2);
  for (ll i = x - 2; i >= 1; --i) invmod[i] = ((invmod[i + 1] % mod) * ((i + 1) % mod)) % mod;
}
 
ll nCr(ll n, ll r) {
  ll lol = (((fact[n] * invmod[r]) % mod) * invmod[n - r]) % mod;
  return lol;
}

ll mul(ll a, ll b) {
	a %= mod; b %= mod;
	return (a * b) % mod;
}

ll add (ll a, ll b) {
	a %= mod; b %= mod;
	return (a + b) % mod;
}
ll calc(int n, int y, int x) {
	ll cur = mul(mul(fact[n], invmod[x]), bigmod(invmod[y], x));
	return cur;
}

void solve() {
	int n; cin >> n;
	ll ans = 0;
	for (int i = 1; 1LL * i * i <= n; ++i) {
		if (n % i == 0) {
			int a = n / i;
			ans = add(ans, calc(n, i, a)); // a teams
			if (a != i) ans = add(ans, calc(n, a, i));
		}
	}

	cout << "Case " << T++ << ": " << ans << "\n";
}

int main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
    cin.tie(0);
    precalcfact(N);
    int t = 1; 
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

    //nc3 = n * (n - 1) * (n - 2) / 6;

5. Problem E

Editorial: N/A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

vector<int> get(int n) {
	vector<int> ans;
	for (int i = 2; i * i <= n; ++i) {
		while (n % i == 0) {
			ans.push_back(i);
			n /= i;
		}
	}
	if (n > 1) ans.push_back(n);
	return ans;
}

multiset<int> Find(int x) {
	multiset<int> down;
	for (int i = 2; i <= x; ++i) {
  		vector<int> factor = get(i);
  		for (int j : factor) down.insert(j);
  	}
  	return down;
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
  	int n, m;
  	while (cin >> n >> m) {
  		if (n == 0 && m == 0) break;
  		int x = n - m;
  		multiset<int> up, down, tmp;
  		up = Find(n);
  		down = Find(x);
  		tmp = Find(m);
  		for (int i : tmp) down.insert(i);
  		while (!down.empty()) {
  			int i = *down.begin();
  			if (up.find(i) != up.end()) {
  				up.erase(up.find(i));
  				down.erase(down.find(i));
  			}
  		}
  		ll ans = 1;
  		for (int K : up) ans *= (1LL * K);
  		//100 things taken 6 at a time is 1192052400 exactly.
  		cout << n << " things taken " << m << " at a time is " << ans << " exactly." << "\n";
  	}
}

    int n, d;
    while(scanf("%d %d", &n, &d)) {
    	if (n == 0 and d == 0) break;
    	d = abs(d);
    	int hi = sqrt(1.00 * d), D = d;
    	map<int, int> prime;
    	for (int i = 2; i <= n; ++i) {
    		int x = i;
    		for (int j = 2; j * j <= x; ++j) {
    			while (x % j == 0) {
    				x /= j;
    				prime[j]++;
    			}
    		}
    		if (x > 1) prime[x]++;
    	}
    	for (int i = 2; 1LL * i * i <= d; ++i) {
    		while (d % i == 0) {
    			prime[i]--;
    			d /= i;
    		}
    	}
    	if (d > 1) prime[d]--;
  //  	debug(prime);
    	ll ans = 1; bool notOk = 0;
    	for (auto i : prime) {
    		ans *= (1LL * (i.second + 1));
    		notOk |= (i.second < 0);
    	}
    	if (notOk) ans = 0;
    	printf("%lld\n", ans);
    }
}

#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

#define print_case  cout << "Case " << tc++ << ": "

const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;
const ll NAX = (ll)2e6 + 3;
int tc = 1;

vector<ll> fact, invmod;

ll bigmod(ll a, ll b) {
  ll result = 1;
  while (b) {
    if (b & 1)
      result = ((result % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    a = ((a % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    b >>= 1;
  }
  return result;
}
void precalcfact(ll x) {
  fact.assign(x, 0);
  invmod.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  invmod[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
  invmod[x-1] = bigmod(fact[x-1], mod-2);
  for(ll i = x-2; i >= 1; --i) invmod[i] = ((invmod[i+1]%mod)*((i+1)%mod))%mod;
}
 
ll nCr(ll n, ll r) {
  ll lol = (((fact[n] * invmod[r]) % mod) * invmod[n - r]) % mod;
  return lol;
}

void solve() {
	ll n, k; cin >> n >> k;
	ll N = n + k - 1;
	print_case;
	cout << nCr(N, n) << "\n";
}

	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1; 
   	precalcfact(NAX);

}

9. Problem I

Editorial: [link](N / A)

Code(C++) 
#include <iostream>

using namespace std;

int main() {
  	unsigned int n, m;
  	while (scanf("%d %d", &n, &m), n || m) {
  	//	if (n == 0 && m == 0) break;
  		double tot = n + m;
  		int mn = min(n, m);
  		double ans = 1.00;
  		while (mn > 0) {
  			ans *= (tot--) / (double(mn));
  			mn--;
  		}
  		printf("%.0lf\n", ans);
  	}
}

  fact.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
}

void solve() {
	ll n, m; cin >> n >> m;
	ll ans = ((fact[n] % mod) * (fact[m] % mod)) % mod;
	if (n == m) ans = ((ans % mod) * (2 % mod)) % mod;

	else cout << ans << "\n";
}

    while(t--) solve();
}

14. Problem N

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <iostream>
#include <string>

constexpr int MAX = 30;
long long dp[MAX + 1][MAX + 1];

std::string find_kth(int A, int B, long long K) {
    if (A == 0) {
        return std::string(B, 'b');
    }
    if (B == 0) {
        return std::string(A, 'a');
    }
    if (K <= dp[A - 1][B]) {
        return std::string("a") + find_kth(A - 1, B, K);
    }
    else {
        return std::string("b") + find_kth(A, B - 1, K - dp[A - 1][B]);
    }
}

int main() {
    int A, B;
    long long K;
    std::cin >> A >> B >> K;
    dp[0][0] = 1;
    for (int i = 0; i <= A; ++i) {
        for (int j = 0; j <= B; ++j) {
            if (i > 0) {
                dp[i][j] += dp[i - 1][j];
            }
            if (j > 0) {
                dp[i][j] += dp[i][j - 1];
            }
        }
    }
    std::cout << find_kth(A, B, K) << '\n';
    return 0;
}

15. Problem O

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include <debug.h>
#else
#define debug(...)
#endif

int n, m, k;

const ll mx = 200505;
const ll mod = 998244353;

vector<ll> fact, invmod;

ll bigmod(ll a, ll b) {
  ll result = 1;
  while (b) {
    if (b & 1)
      result = ((result % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    a = ((a % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    b >>= 1;
  }
  return result;
}
void precalcfact(ll x) {
  fact.assign(x, 0);
  invmod.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  invmod[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
  invmod[x-1] = bigmod(fact[x-1], mod-2);
  for(ll i = x-2; i >= 1; --i) invmod[i] = ((invmod[i + 1] % mod) * ((i+1) % mod)) % mod;
}
 
ll nCr(ll n, ll r) {
  ll lol = (((fact[n] * invmod[r]) % mod) * invmod[n - r]) % mod;
  return lol;
}

ll mul(ll a, ll b, ll c) {
	return ((((a % mod) * (b % mod)) % mod) * (c % mod)) % mod;
}

void solve() {
	cin >> n >> m >> k;
	ll ans = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i <= k; ++i) {
		ll cur = mul(nCr(n - 1, i), m, bigmod(m - 1, n - i - 1));
		ans = ((ans % mod) + (cur % mod)) % mod;
	}
	cout << ans << "\n";
}

int main() {
	ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  	cin.tie(0);
  	precalcfact(mx);
    int t = 1; 
//    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

16. Problem P

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>

using namespace std;
using ll = long long;

#ifdef LOCAL
#include "H:\code\codeforces\debug.h"
#else
#define debug(...)
#define sdebug(...)
#endif

const ll mod = (ll)1e9 + 7;
const int N  = (int)1e7 + 2;

int x, y;

ll ans = 1;

vector<ll> fact, invmod;

ll bigmod(ll a, ll b) {
  ll result = 1;
  while (b) {
    if (b & 1)
      result = ((result % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    a = ((a % mod) * (a % mod)) % mod;
    b >>= 1;
  }
  return result;
}

void precalcfact(ll x) {
  fact.assign(x, 0);
  invmod.assign(x, 0);
  fact[0] = 1;
  invmod[0] = 1;
  for (ll i = 1; i < x; ++i) {
    fact[i] = ((fact[i - 1] % mod) * (i % mod)) % mod;
  }
  invmod[x - 1] = bigmod(fact[x - 1], mod - 2);
  for (ll i = x - 2; i >= 1; --i) invmod[i] = ((invmod[i + 1] % mod) * ((i + 1) % mod)) % mod;
}
 
ll nCr(ll n, ll r) {
  ll lol = (((fact[n] * invmod[r]) % mod) * invmod[n - r]) % mod;
  return lol;
}

ll mul(ll a, ll b) {
	a %= mod; b %= mod;
	return (a * b) % mod;
}

void primeFactor(int n) {
	for (int i = 2; 1LL * i * i <= n; ++i) {
		int cnt = 0;
		while (n % i == 0) {
			n /= i;
			cnt++;
		}
		ans = mul(ans, nCr(cnt + y - 1,  y - 1));
	}
	if (n > 1) ans = mul(ans, nCr(1 + y - 1,  y - 1));
}

void solve() {
	cin >> x >> y;
	ans = 1;
	primeFactor(x);
	cout << mul(ans, bigmod(2, y - 1)) << "\n";
}

int main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
    cin.tie(0);
    int t = 1;
    precalcfact(N);
    cin >> t;
    while(t--) solve();
}

Code(C++) 
//Credit : https://blog.actorsfit.com/a?ID=00550-36d964b7-32fb-4926-8a64-e9c8f44c19cf
#include <iostream>
#include <cstring>
#define max 125
#define nummax 120
using namespace std;

int res[max];
int t[max];

int main()
{
    int n;
    for(int i = 0;i < max;i++)
        res[i] = 1;    
    memset(t,0,sizeof(t));
    for(int i = 2;i <= nummax;i++)
    {
        for(int j = 0;j <= nummax;j++)
            for(int k = 0;k + j <= nummax;k += i)
            {
                t[j + k] += res[j];
            }    
        memcpy(res,t,sizeof(t));
        memset(t,0,sizeof(t));
    }
    while(cin >> n)
    {
        cout << res[n] << endl;
    }    
    return 0;
}
